Serialized Form

  • Package epoetics.core

    • Class epoetics.core.Annotation extends Linguistic_Element implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • color

          java.lang.String color
          The color for representing an annotation in a tool.

        • type

          java.lang.String type
          The main type of the annotation.

        • sub_type

          java.lang.String sub_type
          The sub-type of the annotation. For example, a main type could be something like "text in quotation marks". The sub-type would then something like "emphasis" or "quotation".

        • note

          java.lang.String note
          A note made by a user.

        • unchecked

          boolean unchecked
          Status of the annotation with respect to whether its type was checked by a user. True means that it has not been checked, false means that is has been checked and its type has been verified as the correct type for this annotation.

        • propability

          double propability
          Probability of the classification of an automatically classified instance to be correct.

        • unchanged

          boolean unchanged
          Status of the annotation with respect to whether its type or sub-type has been changed by a user.

    • Class epoetics.core.Chapter extends Linguistic_Element implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • title

          java.lang.String title
          The tile of the chapter.

        • start_sentence

          int start_sentence
          The index of the sentence the chapter starts with. More precisely, the sentence which contains the start offset of the chapter.

        • end_sentence

          int end_sentence
          The index of the sentence the chapter ends with. More precisely, the sentence which contains the end offset of the chapter.

        • offset_to_token_map

        • pos

          java.lang.String pos
          The part-of-speech tag of the token.
